{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place orange zest, orange juice, honey and wasabi paste (optional) into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>6-7 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>, <strong>without measuring cup<\/strong>, until a thick glaze consistency is achieved. Transfer orange glaze into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place parsley, dill and coriander into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place salmon into Varoma dish and tray, season with salt and pepper and set aside.","Place leek, oil and butter into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then sauté <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add buckwheat, verjuice, water and stock paste into mixing bowl. Place Varoma with salmon into position. Brush salmon fillets with half of the reserved orange glaze, then secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1.5<\/nobr>.","Check to see if salmon fillets are cooked to your liking. If salmon is cooked, transfer into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm. If salmon is not cooked, leave fillets in Varoma and set Varoma aside.","Add lemon juice and reserved chopped herbs to mixing bowl, then season to taste with a little extra salt and pepper if necessary.","Place Varoma back into position, then place asparagus into the Varoma dish and onto the Varoma tray arranging around the salmon if applicable. Secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>3-5 min\/Varoma\/\/speed 1.5<\/nobr>, or until salmon and asparagus are cooked to your liking. Set Varoma aside.","Add cashews (optional) and pepitas or sunflower seeds to mixing bowl and combine <nobr>1 min\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Place buckwheat and steamed asparagus onto a plate and top with salmon fillets. Brush salmon fillets with remaining orange glaze, then garnish with crumbled goat's cheese and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 tsp orange zest","100 g orange juice (approx. 1 orange)","30 g honey","¼ tsp wasabi paste, to taste (optional)","4 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","2 sprigs fresh dill, leaves only","4 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only","4 fresh boneless, skinless salmon fillets (approx. 500-600 g total)","1 - 2 pinches sea salt, plus extra to taste","1 - 2 pinches ground black pepper, plus extra to taste","1 leek, white part only, cut into quarters (approx. 160 g)","20 g extra virgin olive oil","20 g butter","300 g buckwheat","100 g verjuice","750 g water","2 tbsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","40 g lemon juice (approx.1 lemon)","1 bunch asparagus, trimmed and cut into halves","100 g roasted, unsalted cashew nuts              (optional)","30 g pepitas","50 g goat's cheese, crumbled"]}],"id":"r83245","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-vsBDoUw9nc0\/XZMyxCMavKI\/AAAAAAAAapQ\/yr1yY2_9cnA70QbsqczsBSw6FTmIwuXLACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ML8xSRssdOQCVV3n.png","title":"Salmon fillets with buckwheat and asparagus","publishedAt":"2015-05-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"63.7 g","fat":"51.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"65.5 g","calories":"4171 kJ \/ 993 kcal"},"usefulItems":"pastry brush, thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, serving platter","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}